>Hello.  I just bought a battery isolator from Napa.  I printed out the
>instructions from the tech library on how to install one of these things but
>things aren't going so smooth.  The bus had some kind of isolator in it
>before but it was much smaller.  It had four wires as described in the tech
>library: one  going to the (+) auxiliary battery, one going to the (+) main


<snip>

Do yourself a favor.  Return the isolator and get a high-power relay that 
is simply wired to the ignition so that it will connect the batteries when 
the key is on.  The relay is available at Camping World and other 
places.  Plenty of info in the archives on this too.

-David

